## Writing Guidelines

### Do's

- ✓ Use passive voice for procedures
- ✓ Use past tense for actions performed
- ✓ Include sufficient detail for replication
- ✓ Specify all parameters (temperature, time, concentration)
- ✓ Cite methods from previous studies when appropriate
- ✓ Use subsections to organize content
- ✓ Include sample sizes and replicates

### Don'ts

- ✗ Include results or interpretation
- ✗ Use vague descriptions ("appropriate amount", "suitable conditions")
- ✗ Omit critical parameters
- ✗ Mix methods and results
- ✗ Use first person excessively ("I did", "we performed")
- ✗ Include unnecessary background

